2w2n A 378 E 297

A redox-regulated disulphide may form between Proprotein convertase subtilisin/kexin type 9 and Low-density lipoprotein receptor at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.

A redox-regulated disulphide may form between Proprotein convertase subtilisin/kexin type 9 and Low-density lipoprotein receptor at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.

Peptide name
Proprotein convertase subtilisin/kexin type 9

2pmw B 626 B 679

A redox-regulated disulphide may form within Proprotein convertase subtilisin/kexin type 9 at these cysteines. However, the redox score of this cysteine pair is lower than any known redox-active disulphide.
